Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.89,0:00:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn, the third Heart Piece…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.06,0:00:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why…? Why…? Why doesn’t it match?! Considering I just got my third Heart Piece after all that…!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.45,0:00:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't that easy to assemble.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.20,0:00:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The heart was divided into several shapes, so only one piece can connect with another.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.87,0:00:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Is that so? Then there's no way I can connect them!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about that, Yuma .
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to find an opponent who uses a Number next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.05,0:00:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason we participated in the Duel Carnival {\i1}is{\i0} to recover Numbers, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.80,0:00:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t that {\i1}your{\i0} problem?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.02,0:00:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you know what, it's always because of you every single time that-
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.52,0:00:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotori!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.32,0:00:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.07,0:01:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell? That AR was really powerful!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.50,0:01:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Yuma! This is real!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.54,0:01:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.09,0:01:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.30,0:01:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep running, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.26,0:01:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the heck is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.26,0:01:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem you are being targeted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.72,0:01:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that possible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.23,0:01:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, Kotori!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.94,0:01:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.69,0:01:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t underestimate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.90,0:01:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can run away from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go, Flying-
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.46,0:01:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.25,0:01:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.46,0:01:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop i-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.93,0:02:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.52,0:02:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she really is after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who in the world is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.73,0:02:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move, move, move!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.57,0:02:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.77,0:02:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We should be all right all the way up here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,End of the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.65,0:02:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys can't run away no-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.43,0:03:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I get closer, I stretch my hand out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.10,0:03:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}towards that shining light leading towards tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I dream of a world that expands from my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.16,0:03:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I haven't a clue of where things like dreams and hopes are at.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.67,0:03:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I run looking for it, I still can't seem to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.13,0:03:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder if I have fallen into a gap of truth and lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.63,0:03:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even so, our grand tale has yet to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.85,0:03:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's move on towards tomorrow, \Neven if our road begins to fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.10,0:03:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will jump forward, before all my\N strength completely drains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.78,0:03:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The closer I get, the further it becomes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.36,0:04:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that truth that I must seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.53,0:04:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's to find hope that we desire from a future unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.70,0:04:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With a heart stronger than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.50,0:04:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll learn to keep running up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.79,0:04:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With the strength to win any battle, \Ndespite just how weak I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.51,0:04:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My purpose is to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.51,0:04:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}with these invaluable friends of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The future of the world expanding\N from my feet with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(536,512)}"Number 29: Railroad Deck, Take Off!\N The Runaway Duelist, Anna"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren’t running away! Are you prepared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:58.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,J-Just hold on! What in the world is going on here, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.02,0:05:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph… You're as dishonest as ever, Yuma Tsukumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.90,0:05:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you Anna?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.45,0:05:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, don’t you remember? Anna Kozuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.49,0:05:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although she transferred to another school two years ago, she always fought with boys, and protected bullied kids. That Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.88,0:05:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we know someone like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't remember me, I'll have to jog your memory!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember, I remember! I think I remember you now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.22,0:05:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why were you chasing Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.39,0:05:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious! It's for revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.89,0:05:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.15,0:05:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma Tsukumo! I... l-like.... y...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.69,0:05:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said! I... love you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.03,0:05:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't tell me Anna...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what on Earth is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I once put glue underneath your shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...drew on your D-Pad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...cut a hole in your swimming trunks...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and put a rock in your riceball.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how mean are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.68,0:06:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.19,0:06:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I transferred two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why I called you out that time, because I wanted to confess to you before I moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you didn’t come… I thought you knew my feelings…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am definitely taking revenge for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.39,0:07:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least allow me to blow you to smithereens!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wa…wait! I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.57,0:07:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don’t have to do all that, do you? Please, if you want revenge that bad… then let’s do it in a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, you can't settle this with her through dueling!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.75,0:07:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.42,0:07:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be your opponent. I knew you would do that, so I started dueling as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.68,0:07:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.43,0:07:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the conditions that you'll belong to {\i1}me{\i0} if I should win!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.43,0:07:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! I won’t lose in a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.19,0:07:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's fight, Yuma Tsukumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.02,0:07:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel Disk, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.69,0:07:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Gazer, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.65,0:07:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AR Vision - Link established.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.70,0:07:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the so-called "human love”? that’s something beyond my understanding…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going first! My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.05,0:08:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I special summon Roaring Express Train Rocket Arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5000 Attack Power!? What a monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.35,0:08:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She summoned heavy-class monster right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card cannot be normal summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.45,0:08:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can only be special summoned from my hand if I do not have any card on my field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And during my turn, it will be destroyed if I don’t send 5 cards from my hand to the graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.04,0:08:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5 cards from your hand? If you send all of them to the graveyard, doesn't that mean your hand will be empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the turn I special summon Roaring Express Train Rocket Arrow, I can declare an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, When this card is face-up on my field, I cannot set other cards either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.10,0:09:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn. Alright, let’s see how you will attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma , we cannot defeat Rocket Arrow in a mere turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Then I will wait for next turn. I set a monster in face-down defense position.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.49,0:09:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I set one card, and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're gonna run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.21,0:09:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I am not running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then behold! My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.46,0:09:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not pay the cost, so Rocket Arrow is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Insanity!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set 5 cards, and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now 5 set cards? Plus no monster means no guard?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.82,0:09:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is she thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, come at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.86,0:10:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No point in over-thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.49,0:10:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.12,0:10:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Gogogo Giant!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I direct attack with Gogogo Giant!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this connects, that’s 2000 points of heavy damage! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Yuma ! She has 5 set cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I destroy all the set cards on my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.39,0:10:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I special summon Snow Plow Engine Hustle Russell!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card cannot be normal summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.24,0:10:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When my opponent declares a direct attack, by destroying all of my Magic and Trap Cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can special summon from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself, Snow Plow Engine Hustle Russell!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.75,0:10:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2500 Attack Points?! Gogogo Giant, stop the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the monster effect of Snow Plow Engine Hustle Russell!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.27,0:11:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For every card on Magic/Trap Zone destroyed by this effect, I can inflict 200 damage to my opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, 5 Cards for 1000 damage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.70,0:11:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.45,0:11:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! 1000 damage to start off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.79,0:11:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's going for Effect Damage, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.50,0:11:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s going on in this duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.17,0:11:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No matter how you look at it, her moves are weird and nonsensical.\N - Yahoo! Yes, I'm gonna win this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yet, they all seem calculated.\N - Hey! It's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Yuma! She’s extraordinarily strong!\N - Hurry it up! You've got nothing else!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.31,0:11:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Shut up! I was just being careless!\N - Hurry up and end your turn already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.52,0:11:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay, here goes!\N - Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.77,0:11:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.24,0:12:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a magic card, Temporary Schedule!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can special summon 1 Machine-Type monster with 3000 or more ATK from my graveyard in defense position!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.37,0:12:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive, Roaring Express Rocket Arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.09,0:12:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That monster again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's got two level 10 monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Yuma! Let’s see if you can stop my Runaway Deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.93,0:12:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overlay the LV10 Rocket Arrow and Snow Plow Engine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.23,0:12:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the overlay network with these two monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.95,0:12:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Super-Heavy Artillery Train Gustav Max!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:13:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3000 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention it’s a Rank 10 Xyz monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a taste of its power! I activate the monster effect of Gustav Max!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.35,0:13:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once per turn, by detaching one overlay unit, this card inflicts 2000 damage to my opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It transformed! Plus, 2000 points of damage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Gustav Max! Ready to fire, Big Canon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.42,0:13:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it! Hooray, hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you only have 1000 Life Points left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This duel is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:13:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn’t forget that promise, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.10,0:14:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here’s the final blow! I attack 2000 ATK Gogogo Giant with Gustav Max, who has 3000 ATK!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.29,0:14:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap activate! Overlay Buster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the end of my Battle Phase, one monster on my field gains 500 ATK!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.14,0:14:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you somehow survived, huh? But it will be over next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.77,0:14:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do? If I take Gustav Max’s effect again, I'll lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.74,0:14:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly speaking, it’s not easy to defeat Gustav Max's 3000 ATK.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:14:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? And what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.29,0:15:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget about your new allies?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.21,0:15:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.63,0:15:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got me some new friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summon Zubaba Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then flip summon Rai-Rider!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overlay the LV3 Zubaba Knight and Rai-Rider!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.16,0:15:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the overlay network with these two monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.58,0:15:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, my new friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.26,0:15:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drumming Fiend Tententempo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Monster with 1000 DEF?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Check it out! Drumming Fiend, Tententempo’s monster effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.35,0:16:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one overlay unit, it can send all Overlay units from my opponent’s Xyz monster to the graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.49,0:16:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for every overlay unit send to the graveyard by this effect, it gains 500 ATK!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drumming Sonic!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Gustav Max can no longer activate its effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus Tententempo will not take battle damage when in defense mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set 2 cards and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How... How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.93,0:16:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you what happens when I get angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.48,0:16:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.85,0:16:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Equipment Magic from my hand, Mechanical Connection!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.90,0:17:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By removing 2 LV8 or higher Machine-type monsters in my graveyard from play, the equipped monster’s ATK doubles!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doubles?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,6000 Attack Points?! Isn’t that even higher than Rocket Arrow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.97,0:17:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What destructive power she has!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.31,0:17:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, due to Mechanical Connection’s effect, when the equipped monster attacks a monster in defense position,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it will inflict piercing damage to my opponent according to the difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means, since Tententempo’s DEF is 1000, if it's attacked, I'll take 5000 damage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.28,0:17:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This match is about to end. Yuma, you're mine now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you gonna cry for forgiveness just like last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cry for forgiveness?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.88,0:17:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean the time I took your card away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.01,0:18:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, if you want your card back, climb on up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Give it back to me!\N -Y ou were crying non-stop since you didn’t know how to climb a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wasn't that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.60,0:18:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I ever do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still playing dumb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not! If I don't remember it, I don't remember it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.36,0:18:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll make you remember with these 6000 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, you have 500 Life Points. If that 6000 Attack Power hits you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.33,0:18:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the time to say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.37,0:18:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it would be fatal to her as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.96,0:18:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.55,0:18:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Yuma ! Here’s the final attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.13,0:18:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Gustav Max! Attack Tententenpo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.06,0:18:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.48,0:18:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gustav Hammer!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma : Trap activate, Recklessness!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.40,0:19:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a monster in defense position was attacked, this card changes it to attack position and continues the battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.12,0:19:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2200 ATK? You can't defeat Gustav Max with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can defeat it like this! I'm gonna bring it to ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.54,0:19:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap activate, Holy Armor, Mirror Mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.75,0:19:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the end of battle phase, the attacked monster will have the ATK of the attacking monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.60,0:19:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their Attack Points are the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, when the Trap card Recklessness destroys an opponent’s monster this way, it will inflict damage to my opponent equal to destroyed monster’s ATK!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.71,0:19:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.00,0:20:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Recklessness’s effect! 6000 damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.94,0:20:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.03,0:20:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you abused those 6000 Attack Points of yours to defeat me when I only had 500 Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.58,0:20:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-If you didn’t do that, you wouldn’t have received huge damage from Recklessness!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.71,0:20:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this may not be the time to say this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the boy you like, Anna, Yoya Tsukune, not Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuya Tsukune?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.73,0:20:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now I remember that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:21:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always cried like a little baby in the teacher’s office.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.86,0:21:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stare~!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.08,0:21:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because your name's so easy to mix up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.41,0:21:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I'll spare you this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah! Hold it, you! Where's the Heart Piece?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.67,0:21:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heart Piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.05,0:21:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost, so you gotta leave that behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.43,0:21:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you come here to participate in the Duel Carnival?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I participate in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.77,0:21:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then say so in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.65,0:21:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God, what a troubling girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.99,0:21:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought it was a little strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.32,0:21:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one would ever like Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.66,0:21:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.58,0:21:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a bit of a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really wish to see that unique dueling again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.38,0:22:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget that girl! I never wanna see her again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.09,0:22:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma Tsukumo, huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.85,0:22:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll remember this, Yuma Tsukumo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.16,0:22:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someone gave me some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.70,0:22:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So I was able to paint a rainbow with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.38,0:22:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to become someone perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.96,0:22:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it's very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.34,0:22:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even with me suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.93,0:22:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't seem to grasp victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.77,0:22:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to bloom!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.23,0:23:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I must be having some kind of weird dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.15,0:23:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But If I must fulfill this,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.69,0:23:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I don't mind being laughed at for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.65,0:23:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since it's because your limits are decided on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.87,0:23:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll show it, overcoming it to tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.87,0:23:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, I'm aiming for the big blue sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.29,0:23:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For all of its glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.02,0:23:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Freesia of Desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.60,0:23:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All of those countless flower petals
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.43,0:23:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They came at the expense of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.10,0:23:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}me being able to reach those heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.21,0:23:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, even though I lost my way today,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.44,0:23:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still yearn for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Freesia of Desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.15,0:23:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vegetable Death Match?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:23:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot declare an attack without eating a vegetable. Some original rules, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.66,0:23:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying I will represent the image of tomatoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.95,0:24:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything's{\i0} turning into tomatoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.96,0:24:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, why aren’t you attacking?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.42,0:24:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The winning formula is completed. But…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be the one to crush your ambition!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.22,0:24:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yuma’s Greatest Ordeal! Fight to Death: Vegetable Death Match!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.01,0:24:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.81,0:24:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma’s dueling hasn’t improved a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.10,0:24:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma: what are you talking about? I'm already really good now!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.44,0:24:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then show me some proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.90,0:24:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alrighty, I Normal Summon Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.49,0:24:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}that's{\i0} your proof!?
